  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Over the last years a number of new endoscopic imaging modalities have been introduced
      (high-definition and virtual chromoendoscopy). Given the theoretical advantage of these new
      imaging techniques, the investigators aimed to investigate their use for the detection of
      polyps during colonoscopy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
